1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,600
welcome back

2
00:00:02,066 --> 00:00:05,800
today we are going to do some progress in the Luv tier

3
00:00:05,933 --> 00:00:09,000
namely we haven't done the new circuits yet

4
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:11,766
and the first thing we have to do to unlock those

5
00:00:11,766 --> 00:00:13,833
is play fetch with the quest book

6
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,533
and that was a breeze

7
00:00:15,666 --> 00:00:16,166
however

8
00:00:16,166 --> 00:00:19,500
the second round starts to be more complicated

9
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:22,066
the first part of the second round is located

10
00:00:22,066 --> 00:00:24,933
on the moon of a planet of another solar system

11
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:26,866
but it was nothing harder than getting there

12
00:00:26,866 --> 00:00:28,700
and processing a new ore

13
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:31,600
the second step requires to find some stuff

14
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:34,500
that we already managed to get a long time ago

15
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:38,600
then we have to do some simple processing steps and it's done

16
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,800
for the last fetch quest

17
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:44,600
we have to change the acid we use to process rare earths

18
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:45,700
however

19
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,233
while that was enough for this fetch quest

20
00:00:48,233 --> 00:00:52,200
it was not enough for the next step with the size we will want it to be

21
00:00:52,466 --> 00:00:54,000
so we also added a new

22
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,300
prioritized way of processing raw lead ores

23
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,066
the next quests

24
00:00:59,066 --> 00:01:02,166
requires to mix together all the stuff we fetched so far

25
00:01:02,166 --> 00:01:06,500
it's nice to know that we didn't fetch all of that stuff for nothing

26
00:01:07,433 --> 00:01:08,300
the issue is that

27
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:09,900
the last step of that stuff

28
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:12,100
has only a chance of succeeding

29
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:16,400
so if we do not want our AE2 system to get stuck

30
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:19,500
due to the expected stuff that failed in the process

31
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:23,666
we shall make a pattern with more inputs than the required ones

32
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:24,466
finally

33
00:01:24,466 --> 00:01:27,500
when we try to craft that over crafted item

34
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:31,633
we find ourselves presented with a huge list of ingredients

35
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:32,566
luckily

36
00:01:32,566 --> 00:01:35,733
our EBF stocked up quite some extra dusts

37
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:37,700
that we can compact manually

38
00:01:38,266 --> 00:01:40,666
and now we can complete the quest

39
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:44,066
and all the extra items we have produced in the meantime

40
00:01:44,066 --> 00:01:45,733
will be useful later on

41
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,933
and everything we did so far

42
00:01:47,933 --> 00:01:50,533
was just preparing the tools and materials

43
00:01:50,533 --> 00:01:52,600
for the real circuitry industry

44
00:01:53,033 --> 00:01:54,933
the circuits we are going to do today

45
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:57,400
are part of the crystal processor series

46
00:01:57,400 --> 00:02:00,233
which starts from emerald crystals

47
00:02:00,633 --> 00:02:01,066
however

48
00:02:01,066 --> 00:02:03,866
making those with emeralds is quite expensive

49
00:02:03,866 --> 00:02:06,000
and has low success chances

50
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:09,500
the better way is with raw crystal chip parts

51
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:12,800
but those parts are made with the crystal we need

52
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:15,700
so we go with the Emerald Way

53
00:02:15,866 --> 00:02:18,800
and here you can see our first failed attempt

54
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:22,033
we keep trying until we get a successful one

55
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,933
now that we have won the crystal lottery

56
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:28,633
we want to use that one crystal to craft a pile more

57
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:30,100
to do so

58
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,500
we have to make a loop where we smash crystals

59
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:36,000
and then make the fragments grow back by using europium

60
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,933
we could do that passively

61
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:41,600
but since we are going to craft europium on demand

62
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:44,533
we also make a pattern for crystal on demand

63
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:47,900
we will input europium for two crystals in the loop

64
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:50,166
so that one crystal will be outputed

65
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:52,800
and one reused to make more crystals

66
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:55,100
there is going to be some extras

67
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,433
but that's a feature not a bug

68
00:02:57,700 --> 00:03:00,933
and once we set up the two looping machines

69
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,233
we just have to input our only crystal

70
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:05,933
and some europium to fill up the machines

71
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:06,866
behold

72
00:03:06,866 --> 00:03:11,466
the legendary mythical secret technique of the crystal multiplication

73
00:03:11,866 --> 00:03:12,333
however

74
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:14,733
to use those crystals as processors

75
00:03:14,733 --> 00:03:18,200
we first have to cook them with some extra crystals

76
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,633
since we can use both Emerald or olivine

77
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:23,600
and we can't make up our mind on which one to use

78
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,933
we do a custom pattern that does both at the same time

79
00:03:27,466 --> 00:03:29,333
once our crystals are cooked

80
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,933
we shoot them with lasers

81
00:03:30,933 --> 00:03:36,133
to get some chips which we can now use to finally have our first crystal processor

82
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:39,000
and here something started to feel weird

83
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,133
for some reason

84
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:41,466
the cost of that circuit

85
00:03:41,466 --> 00:03:44,433
seems to be 6 times higher than expected

86
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,266
and the reason for that is that

87
00:03:46,266 --> 00:03:50,700
we are probably supposed to use a dedicated circuit assembling line

88
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,233
to craft those circuits

89
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,733
but to use that

90
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:56,200
we also need a circuit imprint

91
00:03:56,633 --> 00:03:59,733
which has to be made out of the circuit we want to make

92
00:03:59,866 --> 00:04:04,500
so we start by making a pattern for a circuit in the expensive way

93
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:06,733
but we do not automate that

94
00:04:06,866 --> 00:04:09,666
we will have the ingredients dropped in a chest

95
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:13,500
so that we will use the expensive way only one time manually

96
00:04:14,266 --> 00:04:16,233
once the ingredients are ready

97
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:20,000
we craft our first crystal processor to use as a sample

98
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:22,666
all we have to do to turn it into an imprint

99
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:25,900
is slice it and then add the stuff we fetched earlier on

100
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:27,833
now that we have the imprint

101
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:31,000
required to make circuits in the not as expensive way

102
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,900
we only need an assembly line where to place it

103
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,400
and after some quick crafting

104
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,633
there we have it

105
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:40,200
all we have to do is place the imprint

106
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,833
and then start making tons of circuits

107
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:44,833
and then something happened

108
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,400
the imprint made it so that this circuit line

109
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:51,000
will only be able to craft this specific processor from now on

110
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,566
even if we break it

111
00:04:52,566 --> 00:04:55,100
there is no way of changing recipe

112
00:04:55,266 --> 00:04:58,666
which means we are going to need a lot of those machines

113
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:00,666
at least one for each recipe

114
00:05:01,133 --> 00:05:03,900
also like the normal assembly line

115
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:06,833
this one wants stuff in the correct place too

116
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:11,666
but since it will only craft one single recipe for its whole life

117
00:05:11,666 --> 00:05:16,700
we can just use a filter system to ensure the ingredients go in the correct slot

118
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:21,466
and now we can slowly craft our first batch of circuits

119
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:22,300
as usual

120
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:24,466
they come in four clustering levels

121
00:05:24,466 --> 00:05:30,400
and we use the first two processors to make a processor assembly in the expensive way

122
00:05:30,866 --> 00:05:31,733
then we slice it

123
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:34,833
to make an imprint for those clustered circuits

124
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:39,333
and we bind forever the imprint to our 2nd Circuit assembling line

125
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:41,066
then we realize that

126
00:05:41,066 --> 00:05:42,100
at some point

127
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:46,100
we will want this setup to work faster than conduits can handle

128
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:50,266
so we instead switch to an AE2 sub network

129
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:52,800
which has virtually infinite throughput

130
00:05:53,266 --> 00:05:55,400
using stocking inputs buses

131
00:05:55,400 --> 00:06:00,066
which will allow the assembler to directly take millions of items at once from AE2

132
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:01,800
that speed will be reached 

133
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,733
thanks to the perfect overclocks

134
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:06,866
that will quadruple the machine speed every tier

135
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,066
for now we go slow

136
00:06:08,633 --> 00:06:10,100
next we prepare everything

137
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:13,900
for crafting the last two clusters of crystal processors

138
00:06:14,266 --> 00:06:18,033
and with that we have about finished the Luv tier

139
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,133
on a side note

140
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:22,133
we can also use the new machinery

141
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:25,000
to make way cheaper HV circuits

142
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:27,733
and we can quickly update all of our patterns

143
00:06:27,733 --> 00:06:31,200
by just changing the way we make the generic HV circuit

144
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:34,000
that is being used by all the patterns

145
00:06:34,466 --> 00:06:34,833
also

146
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:39,666
since all of our CPUs are waiting for the slow 4 circuit assemblers

147
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:43,400
we can make one more circuit assembling line in circuit assembler mode

148
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,466
for generic simple circuits

149
00:06:45,866 --> 00:06:48,933
the trick here is to have an advanced stocking input bus

150
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:50,533
with auto pull enabled

151
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:55,933
that will turn the whole connected ae2 storage into an input bus for that machine

152
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,466
and with that

153
00:06:57,466 --> 00:07:00,133
we are now making in five seconds the circuits

154
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:03,000
that were taking 80 seconds and a clean room

155
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:03,933
with that

156
00:07:03,933 --> 00:07:06,666
I think we can move to the ZPM tier

157
00:07:06,666 --> 00:07:11,133
where we already rushed some things that were required for our reactor build

158
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,133
and here instead of playing fetch

159
00:07:14,133 --> 00:07:16,733
we play guess the item with some riddles

160
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:18,700
since I'm not good at riddles

161
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,866
whose solutions are items I don't have access to

162
00:07:21,866 --> 00:07:23,500
we go with the glutton way

163
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:26,933
hopefully the ingredients in our farmhouse

164
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:30,500
that hasn't been checked for 9 episodes didn't go bad

165
00:07:31,066 --> 00:07:34,900
we quickly cook some of the food that this hardworking dude wants

166
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:38,733
but then we realize that we do not have any lime for his dessert

167
00:07:39,266 --> 00:07:41,033
since he is also picky

168
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:41,500
I guess

169
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:44,700
the lesson here is not to give candy to strangers

170
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,833
they might not like the flavor you have at your disposal

171
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,700
going back to our new quest page

172
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:53,400
I think we can finally get closer to the midgame

173
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,633
with this cool looking block quest

174
00:07:56,466 --> 00:08:00,666
and since those blocks require a ZPM assembler in a clean room

175
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:03,400
we have to either relocate a ZPM assembler

176
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,033
in a processing array or in a clean room

177
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:10,800
but we will probably want to get a new one to speed up things

178
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,533
and since we are low on europium

179
00:08:13,533 --> 00:08:17,400
we quickly build a fusion reactor that AE2 will manage

180
00:08:17,866 --> 00:08:21,100
but you should always do more machines than required

181
00:08:21,466 --> 00:08:22,100
and with that

182
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,733
we have our ZPM assembler

183
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:25,800
that we shall place in a clean room

184
00:08:26,466 --> 00:08:30,866
and now we can start working on crafting those cool looking blocks

185
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:34,266
once we have made some of each one

186
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:37,233
we have to choose what machine we shall build with those

187
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:41,266
and I think we shall start from the active transformer

188
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:43,400
however

189
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:47,666
it looks that somehow we missed the monazite for crafting it

190
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,033
to find out how and why

191
00:08:50,033 --> 00:08:51,466
we can check the crafting tree

192
00:08:51,466 --> 00:08:54,533
and follow the branch with the missing ingredient

193
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,300
and it turns out

194
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:59,333
we are still using monazite for making helium

195
00:09:00,266 --> 00:09:01,333
as a quick fix

196
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:04,066
we relocate a miner on a nice beach

197
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:06,400
that miner is of the highest tier

198
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:10,666
and can mine an area of 300 by 300 blocks

199
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:13,700
exactly the range of our or prospector

200
00:09:13,733 --> 00:09:17,266
making it so that the prospector shows exactly what we will dig

201
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,600
and upgrading our miners broke the transceiver cover

202
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:23,933
once we replace it

203
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:26,033
we can see again our stats

204
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:28,766
one other source of helium we can use

205
00:09:28,766 --> 00:09:30,900
is from a multi block plasma turbine

206
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:32,666
running on helium plasma

207
00:09:33,466 --> 00:09:36,533
and now that we have crafted our new transformer

208
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:40,200
we can start fixing all of the spaghetti under our base

209
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:43,933
we can now have one single high power cable

210
00:09:43,933 --> 00:09:45,633
being spread by the transformer

211
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:47,933
into many lower power cables

212
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:52,033
and thus we spend some time rewiring our base

213
00:09:52,666 --> 00:09:55,533
the next thing we can craft with the cool looking blocks

214
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:56,733
is a data bank

215
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,100
this one is a multi block

216
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,233
that can take many data hatches

217
00:10:01,233 --> 00:10:05,433
enough to contain all of the researched recipes we have done so far

218
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:09,066
then using optical fiber cables

219
00:10:09,066 --> 00:10:12,000
it will spread the data to many assembly lines

220
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:12,633
that way

221
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:16,800
instead of having a limit of 17 recipes for each assembly line

222
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:20,233
and having to research an item once for every assembly line

223
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:22,833
we can do everything on every assembly line

224
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,433
and from the AE2 side

225
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:29,600
instead of crafting copies of the same pattern for each assembly line

226
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,066
we can use a peer to peer interface

227
00:10:32,866 --> 00:10:35,300
all the interface we link to the first one

228
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:37,200
will share the same recipes

229
00:10:38,066 --> 00:10:38,300
thus

230
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:40,833
we can now make a lot of different items

231
00:10:40,833 --> 00:10:43,533
simultaneously in many assembly lines

232
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,833
and with that

233
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:47,333
I think we can move on with the progression

234
00:10:47,633 --> 00:10:50,266
after completing the superconductor quest

235
00:10:50,266 --> 00:10:51,033
usually

236
00:10:51,033 --> 00:10:54,066
we would expect to unlock the Energy Hatch quest

237
00:10:54,266 --> 00:10:55,500
however nowadays

238
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:58,533
it looks like it is being gated by something new

239
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:00,033
and the issue seems to be

240
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:02,733
with the Nano Power integrated circuit

241
00:11:02,966 --> 00:11:04,166
to work its wafer

242
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:06,300
we need some flocculated water

243
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:08,066
to flocculate water

244
00:11:08,066 --> 00:11:11,100
we have to not get distracted by the cool looking UI

245
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:14,233
and to get a flocculation purification unit

246
00:11:14,533 --> 00:11:17,233
and I think we can all see where this is going

247
00:11:17,733 --> 00:11:21,500
that thing is probably going to need its dedicated episode

248
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:22,533
bye bye

249
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,600
欢迎回来！

250
00:00:02,066 --> 00:00:05,800
今天我们要推进一下 LuV 的进度

251
00:00:05,933 --> 00:00:09,000
新电路都还没做呢

252
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:11,766
要做的第一件事

253
00:00:11,766 --> 00:00:13,833
便是跟着任务书解锁它们

254
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,533
这可再轻松不过

255
00:00:15,666 --> 00:00:16,166
然而

256
00:00:16,166 --> 00:00:19,500
第二轮开始变得复杂

257
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:22,066
要达成的第一步

258
00:00:22,066 --> 00:00:24,933
位于另一个太阳系行星的卫星上（罗斯128ba）

259
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:26,866
不过最大的难点也只是到达那儿

260
00:00:26,866 --> 00:00:28,700
并加工新矿石

261
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:31,600
第二步需要找到一些东西

262
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:34,500
不过很久以前我们就已经获得了

263
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:38,600
然后做一些简单的处理步骤就搞定了

264
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,800
而最后一个任务

265
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:44,600
必须改变用来处理稀土的酸

266
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:45,700
不过

267
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,233
虽然已经获得了任务要求的量

268
00:00:48,233 --> 00:00:52,200
但对我们要达到的规模来说还远远不够

269
00:00:52,466 --> 00:00:54,000
所以我们还添加了一个新的

270
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,300
铅粉碎矿的优先处理产线

271
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,066
下一个任务

272
00:00:59,066 --> 00:01:02,166
需要把目前所有的原料合在一起

273
00:01:02,166 --> 00:01:06,500
很高兴知道我们的努力并没有白费

274
00:01:07,433 --> 00:01:08,300
问题是

275
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:09,900
那东西的最后一步

276
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:12,100
是一个概率配方

277
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:16,400
因为此配方很可能在处理中失败

278
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:19,500
所以如果不想让 AE 卡住

279
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:23,666
我们需要一个输入比所需量大的样板

280
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:24,466
最后

281
00:01:24,466 --> 00:01:27,500
当我们试图制作过量的物品时

282
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:31,633
却发现缺乏了大量的碲粉

283
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:32,566
幸运地

284
00:01:32,566 --> 00:01:35,733
我们的高炉中存储了大量的副产粉尘

285
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:37,700
可以手动压缩它们

286
00:01:38,266 --> 00:01:40,666
现在我们可以完成任务了

287
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:44,066
我们在任务中制作的东西

288
00:01:44,066 --> 00:01:45,733
以后都会有用的

289
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,933
不过迄今为止所做的一切

290
00:01:47,933 --> 00:01:50,533
都只是在准备阶段

291
00:01:50,533 --> 00:01:52,600
还未开始真正制作

292
00:01:53,033 --> 00:01:54,933
我们今天要做的电路

293
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:57,400
是晶体处理器系列的一部分

294
00:01:57,400 --> 00:02:00,233
从使用绿宝石开始

295
00:02:00,633 --> 00:02:01,066
然而

296
00:02:01,066 --> 00:02:03,866
用绿宝石太贵了

297
00:02:03,866 --> 00:02:06,000
而且成功概率也低

298
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:09,500
更好的方法是用晶体芯片碎片来循环

299
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:12,800
但它们又需要晶体芯片原料

300
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:15,700
所以我们先用绿宝石做

301
00:02:15,866 --> 00:02:18,800
你可以看到第一次的失败尝试

302
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:22,033
保持努力，直到成功获得一个

303
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,933
既然我们中了水晶彩票

304
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:28,633
我们想用那一块晶体芯片原料复制出一堆

305
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:30,100
要这样做

306
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,500
我们必须先将其打碎

307
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:36,000
再通过铕让其完成一次循环生长

308
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,933
这可以做个被动产线

309
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:41,600
但既然我们要按需生产铕

310
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:44,533
我们便按需制作晶体样板

311
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:47,900
我们将为循环中的两个晶体输入铕

312
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:50,166
这样便会输出一个晶体芯片原料

313
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:52,800
另一个则被重复使用以制造更多晶体

314
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:55,100
这会有些额外的产物

315
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,433
但那是特性而不是 BUG

316
00:02:57,700 --> 00:03:00,933
一旦安装好了两台循环机器

317
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,233
我们只需要输入唯一的晶体

318
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:05,933
和一些铕来填满机器

319
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:06,866
敬请见证

320
00:03:06,866 --> 00:03:11,466
传说中的晶体倍增神秘科技

321
00:03:11,866 --> 00:03:12,333
然而

322
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:14,733
要使用这些晶体作为处理器

323
00:03:14,733 --> 00:03:18,200
我们必须用一些额外的水晶来处理它们

324
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,633
不过绿宝石和橄榄石都在考虑范围内

325
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:23,600
不太好决定用哪一个

326
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,933
我们做了一个同时发配两类晶体的样板

327
00:03:27,466 --> 00:03:29,333
一旦晶体处理完毕

328
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,933
再通过激光蚀刻

329
00:03:30,933 --> 00:03:36,133
便获得能用来制作晶体处理器的芯片

330
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:39,000
这配方有点怪

331
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,133
出于某种原因

332
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:41,466
电路板的成本

333
00:03:41,466 --> 00:03:44,433
似乎比预期高6倍

334
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,266
原因是

335
00:03:46,266 --> 00:03:50,700
我们应当使用电路装配线

336
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,233
来制作那些电路板

337
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,733
而要使用它

338
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:56,200
我们还需要一个压印电路

339
00:03:56,633 --> 00:03:59,733
它必须由我们想要制作的电路制成

340
00:03:59,866 --> 00:04:04,500
所以我们首先以昂贵的方式为电路制作压印电路

341
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:06,733
但我们不自动化这个步骤

342
00:04:06,866 --> 00:04:09,666
而是把原料放进箱子里

343
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:13,500
这样就只需要用一次这个高价配方了

344
00:04:14,266 --> 00:04:16,233
一旦材料准备好

345
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:20,000
我们制作了第一个晶体处理器用作样品

346
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:22,666
把它变成压印电路的步骤是

347
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:25,900
将其切片，然后加上我们之前拿到的东西

348
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:27,833
现在我们有了压印电路

349
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:31,000
可以用廉价的方式制作电路板了

350
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,900
我们就差一条电路装配线了

351
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,400
经过快速制作

352
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,633
它来喽

353
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:40,200
我们把压印电路放进去

354
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,833
然后开始制作成吨的电路板

355
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:44,833
但有些事需要注意

356
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,400
这条电路装配线因为压印电路

357
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:51,000
已经只能制作这一种电路板了

358
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,566
即使拆除主方块

359
00:04:52,566 --> 00:04:55,100
也不会改变其配方

360
00:04:55,266 --> 00:04:58,666
这意味着我们将大量需要这种机器

361
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:00,666
每个配方至少一台

362
00:05:01,133 --> 00:05:03,900
像普通的装配线一样

363
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:06,833
它也需要将物品输入正确的仓室

364
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:11,666
但是因为它一生只能制作一个配方

365
00:05:11,666 --> 00:05:16,700
我们可以使用过滤系统来确保物至其位

366
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:21,466
现在我们可以慢慢制作第一批电路了

367
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:22,300
像往常一样

368
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:24,466
它们有四个级别

369
00:05:24,466 --> 00:05:30,400
我们用前两个晶体处理器以昂贵的方式做一个集群

370
00:05:30,866 --> 00:05:31,733
然后切片

371
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:34,833
为这电路板做出压印电路

372
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:39,333
将它绑定到第二条电路装配线上

373
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:41,066
然后我们意识到

374
00:05:41,066 --> 00:05:42,100
在之后

375
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:46,100
我们希望这个产线比管道能处理的更快

376
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:50,266
所以我们改为使用 AE 子网

377
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:52,800
它几乎具有无限的吞吐量

378
00:05:53,266 --> 00:05:55,400
使用存储输入总线

379
00:05:55,400 --> 00:06:00,066
允许装配线一次性从 AE 中抽取数以万计的物品

380
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:01,800
这样的速度是可能的

381
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,733
多亏了无损超频

382
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:06,866
每升压一次机器速度便翻四倍

383
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,066
现在它还是比较慢

384
00:06:08,633 --> 00:06:10,100
接下来我们准备好一切

385
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:13,900
制作晶体处理器系列最后两个电路板

386
00:06:14,266 --> 00:06:18,033
这样我们就快完成了 LuV 的任务了

387
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,133
顺便说一句

388
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:22,133
我们也可以使用新机器

389
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:25,000
制造更便宜的 HV 电路

390
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:29,766
只需要改变制作任意 HV 电路板的配方

391
00:06:29,766 --> 00:06:34,000
就能将所有使用 HV 电路板的样板轻松更新

392
00:06:34,466 --> 00:06:34,833
而且

393
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:37,133
因为所有的 CPU 都在等待

394
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:39,666
那慢吞吞的 4 并行电路组装机

395
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:43,400
我们可以做一条电路组装机模式的电路装配线

396
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,466
来普适地做简单电路

397
00:06:45,866 --> 00:06:48,933
这里的诀窍是用一个进阶存储输入总线

398
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:50,533
启用自动拉取

399
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:53,900
这将把整个连接的 AE 存储

400
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,933
变成这台机器的输入总线

401
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,466
有了这个

402
00:06:57,466 --> 00:07:00,133
我们便可以在五秒内完成制作

403
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:03,000
之前需要在超净间内等待 80 秒的电路

404
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:03,933
有了那个

405
00:07:03,933 --> 00:07:06,666
我想我们进入 ZPM 电压了

406
00:07:06,666 --> 00:07:11,133
我们已经仓促完成了建造反应堆所需的任务

407
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,133
我们在这不是跟着任务收集物品

408
00:07:14,133 --> 00:07:16,733
而是做个猜谜游戏

409
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:18,700
由于我不擅长猜谜语

410
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,866
而谜底是我们无法获取的东西

411
00:07:21,866 --> 00:07:23,500
我们先满足出题人的食欲

412
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:26,933
希望我们农舍里的配料

413
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:30,500
在九集时间流逝下没有变质

414
00:07:31,066 --> 00:07:34,900
我们很快做出这个勤劳的家伙想要的一些食物

415
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:38,733
但很快发现我们没有他想要的酸橙

416
00:07:39,266 --> 00:07:41,033
既然他也很挑剔

417
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:41,500
我猜

418
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:44,700
今天的教训是不要给陌生人糖果

419
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,833
他们可能不喜欢你的口味

420
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,700
返回新的任务页面

421
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:53,400
我想我们已经进入游戏中期了

422
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,633
有了这些看上去很酷的任务

423
00:07:56,466 --> 00:08:00,666
由于这些材料需要超净间环境的 ZPM 组装机处理

424
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:03,400
我们得重新在处理阵列或者超净间中

425
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,033
做一个 ZPM 组装机

426
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:10,800
但我们可能需要一个新玩意来提高效率

427
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,533
不过我们的铕存量太少

428
00:08:13,533 --> 00:08:17,400
我们快速建造一个由 AE 管理的聚变反应堆

429
00:08:17,866 --> 00:08:21,100
多堆点机器总是好的

430
00:08:21,466 --> 00:08:22,100
有了这个

431
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,733
我们便获得了ZPM组装机

432
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:25,800
将其放置在超净间中

433
00:08:26,466 --> 00:08:30,866
现在便可以考虑制作那些很酷的方块了

434
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:34,266
一旦完成一些方块的制作

435
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:37,233
我们就要决定要拿它们做什么机器了

436
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:41,266
我认为有源变压器是第一位的

437
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:43,400
然而

438
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:47,666
看起来我们缺少独居石来制作它

439
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,033
要知道为什么

440
00:08:50,033 --> 00:08:51,466
我们可以检查合成树

441
00:08:51,466 --> 00:08:54,533
并跟随缺失成分的分支

442
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,300
结果证明

443
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:59,333
我们仍在使用独居石制造氦气

444
00:09:00,266 --> 00:09:01,333
作为快速解决方案

445
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:04,066
我们在一个风景宜人的海滩上拍下采矿厂

446
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:06,400
这个 IV 级采矿场

447
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:10,666
可以开采 300x300 的方块

448
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:13,700
而这正是我们探矿仪的范围

449
00:09:13,733 --> 00:09:17,266
这样探矿仪就能准确地看到我们要挖的东西

450
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,600
升级采矿场导致传感器卡片坏了

451
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:23,933
将其更换

452
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:26,033
我们便可以再看到数据

453
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:28,766
我们可以用的另一种氦源

454
00:09:28,766 --> 00:09:30,900
来自多方块等离子涡轮机

455
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:32,666
它靠氦等离子体运行

456
00:09:33,466 --> 00:09:36,533
现在我们已经制作好了新变压器

457
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:40,200
可以开始修整基地下的凌乱电线了

458
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:43,933
现在可以用一根大功率电缆

459
00:09:43,933 --> 00:09:45,633
通过有源变压器

460
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:47,933
输出多根低功率电线

461
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:52,033
因此，我们花了一些时间重新给基地布线

462
00:09:52,666 --> 00:09:55,533
接下来用这些好看方块可以做的结构

463
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:56,733
是一个数据库

464
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,100
它是一个多方块结构

465
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,233
可以存储多种闪存

466
00:10:01,233 --> 00:10:05,433
足以包含我们迄今为止所做的所有研究

467
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:09,066
然后使用光纤

468
00:10:09,066 --> 00:10:12,000
它可以将闪存数据传输给多个装配线

469
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:12,633
用这个方式

470
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:16,800
装配线不再只能做 17 个配方

471
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:20,233
也不需要每个装配线都研究一次

472
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:22,833
任意一条装配线都可以随意制作物品了

473
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,433
对于 AE

474
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:29,600
不需要每个装配线都写一样的配方

475
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,066
我们可以使用 p2p 接口

476
00:10:32,866 --> 00:10:35,300
所有连接到第一个 p2p 接口的接口

477
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:37,200
都会共享相同的样板

478
00:10:38,066 --> 00:10:38,300
因此

479
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:40,833
在多个装配线下

480
00:10:40,833 --> 00:10:43,533
我们可以同时制作多个物品

481
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,833
有了这个

482
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:47,333
我想我们可以推进度

483
00:10:47,633 --> 00:10:50,266
完成超导任务后

484
00:10:50,266 --> 00:10:51,033
通常

485
00:10:51,033 --> 00:10:54,066
我们希望可以解锁能源仓任务

486
00:10:54,266 --> 00:10:55,500
然而如今

487
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:58,533
它看起来像是被新的东西锁住了

488
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:00,033
似乎是

489
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:02,733
纳米功率 IC 晶圆的问题

490
00:11:02,966 --> 00:11:04,166
为了获得它

491
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:06,300
我们需要一些絮凝水

492
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:08,066
使水絮凝

493
00:11:08,066 --> 00:11:11,100
我们不能被酷炫的 UI 分散注意力

494
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:14,233
想获得絮凝净化单元

495
00:11:14,533 --> 00:11:17,233
